R Notebook

# Load required libraries
library(palmerpenguins)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(scales)

# Load and clean the data
data(penguins)
penguins_clean <- penguins %>% drop_na()
# 1. Highly Objective: Raw Scatter Plot
# Minimal styling, shows raw data points
objective_scatter <- ggplot(penguins_clean, 
    aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  labs(
    title = "Raw Data: Bill Dimensions",
    x = "Bill Length (mm)",
    y = "Bill Depth (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10)
  )

# 2. Medium Objectivity: Species-Colored Scatter with Confidence Ellipses
species_scatter <- ggplot(penguins_clean, 
    aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm, color = species)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
  stat_ellipse(level = 0.95) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  labs(
    title = "Species Clusters with Confidence Ellipses",
    x = "Bill Length (mm)",
    y = "Bill Depth (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.position = "right"
  )
# 3. Lower Objectivity: Stylized Density Plot
density_plot <- ggplot(penguins_clean, 
    aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm, color = species)) +
  stat_density_2d(aes(fill = species), geom = "polygon", alpha = 0.4) +
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  labs(
    title = "Density Distribution by Species",
    x = "Bill Length (mm)",
    y = "Bill Depth (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    legend.position = "right"
  )
# 4. Abstract Representation: Summarized Boxplots
abstract_boxes <- ggplot(penguins_clean, 
    aes(x = species, y = bill_length_mm, fill = species)) +
  geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  labs(
    title = "Bill Length Distribution by Species",
    x = "Species",
    y = "Bill Length (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    legend.position = "none"
  )

# 5. Highly Abstracted: Mean Points with Error Bars
summary_stats <- penguins_clean %>%
  group_by(species) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_length = mean(bill_length_mm),
    se_length = sd(bill_length_mm) / sqrt(n())
  )

abstract_summary <- ggplot(summary_stats, 
    aes(x = reorder(species, mean_length), y = mean_length, fill = species)) +
  geom_point(size = 4, shape = 21) +
  geom_errorbar(
    aes(ymin = mean_length - se_length, 
        ymax = mean_length + se_length), 
    width = 0.2
  ) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
  labs(
    title = "Mean Bill Length by Species",
    x = "Species",
    y = "Mean Bill Length (mm)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    legend.position = "none"
  )
# Print all plots
print(objective_scatter)

print(species_scatter)

print(density_plot)

print(abstract_boxes)

print(abstract_summary)
